      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "Define sample text, transform it using the fitted TF-IDF vectorizer, and predict the sentiment using the trained model.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "7a5aae8b",
        "outputId": "c32d4916-383c-4ef5-a446-7c9f631b0035"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Define sample text\n",
        "sample_text = [\"This movie was fantastic!\", \"This movie was terrible.\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Transform sample text using the fitted TF-IDF vectorizer\n",
        "sample_vec = tfidf.transform(sample_text)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Predict the sentiment of the transformed sample text\n",
        "predictions = model.predict(sample_vec)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Print the predictions\n",
        "print(\"Predictions:\", predictions)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 12,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Predictions: [2 2]\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d0a4c450"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Summary:\n",
        "\n",
        "### Data Analysis Key Findings\n",
        "\n",
        "*   The IMDB dataset was successfully downloaded and extracted.\n",
        "*   The training data was loaded using `sklearn.datasets.load_files`.\n",
        "*   Text data was preprocessed by decoding from UTF-8 and converting to lowercase.\n",
        "*   Features were extracted using `TfidfVectorizer` with English stop words and a maximum of 10000 features.\n",
        "*   The data was split into training and testing sets with a test size of 20%.\n",
        "*   A Logistic Regression model was trained with `max_iter=1000`.\n",
        "*   The model achieved an accuracy of approximately 69% on the test set.\n",
        "*   The classification report showed varying performance across classes, with better results for class 2.\n",
        "*   Predictions were made on new sample texts, but both samples (\"This movie was fantastic!\" and \"This movie was terrible.\") were predicted as class 2.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Insights or Next Steps\n",
        "\n",
        "*   The model's prediction of class 2 for both positive and negative sample texts suggests an issue. It's likely that the label '2' corresponds to the positive class in the dataset, but the model is failing to correctly classify the negative example. Further investigation into the dataset's label mapping and the model's performance on negative examples is needed.\n",
        "*   Consider exploring other machine learning models or techniques for sentiment analysis that might offer better performance, especially in distinguishing between positive and negative sentiments.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
